32:["$","p","p-31",{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"DAO treasuries don't have to choose between idle stables and directional bets. Cross-exchange funding rate arbitrage offers a middle path: market-neutral, stablecoin-denominated yield from structural market inefficiencies."}]
33:["$","p","p-32",{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"It's not risk-free — exchange counterparty risk is real, and yields vary with market conditions. But for treasuries sitting on stables earning 2% while operational costs eat into runway, it's worth evaluating whether a portion of that capital could work harder."}]
34:["$","p","p-33",{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"The best treasury strategies aren't about maximizing yield. They're about matching revenue to expenses: stablecoins in, stablecoins out, independent of what the market does."}]
